PN,30802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774033869
OL,3,CWarm and sunny weekend - but a cold
OL,4,Csnap brings snow risk next week
OL,6,FHigh pressure, which has given us the
OL,7,Fglorious conditions this week, remains
OL,8,Fin control, keeping things settled. So
OL,9,Fexpect plenty of sunshine, and mild
OL,10,Fconditions - especially across
OL,11,Fsouthern and eastern areas.
OL,13,FTemperatures should reach around 14C,
OL,14,Fso a far cry from the 20C we saw on
OL,15,FWednesday, but still very reasonable
OL,16,Ffor the time of year.
OL,18,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,19,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,20,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,21,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774033869
OL,3,CWarm and sunny weekend - but a cold
OL,4,Csnap brings snow risk next week
OL,6,FIt's worth bearing in mind that the
OL,7,Fsunshine might take a little while to
OL,8,Fget going in the mornings - especially
OL,9,Ftowards the south east - as mist and
OL,10,Ffog forming overnight is likely to
OL,11,Ftake some time to burn off.
OL,13,FWill it stay warm next week?
OL,15,FSadly not.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
