PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774033869
OL,3,CWarm and sunny weekend - but a cold
OL,4,Csnap brings snow risk next week
OL,6,FThe Met Office is forecasting a return
OL,7,Fto colder, more unsettled conditions:
OL,8,Fsnow, bringing wintry showers, icy
OL,9,Fpatches, and frost, particularly
OL,10,Facross northern and western parts of
OL,11,Fthe UK.
OL,13,FWhy is it getting colder again?
OL,15,FAs always, it's predominantly down to
OL,16,Fwind direction.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774033869
OL,3,CWarm and sunny weekend - but a cold
OL,4,Csnap brings snow risk next week
OL,6,FOver the last week we've enjoyed a
OL,7,Fwarm southeasterly feed of air across
OL,8,Fthe UK, which has dragged mild
OL,9,Ftemperatures in from the near
OL,10,Fcontinent.
OL,12,FOver the weekend, the winds start to
OL,13,Fveer more southwesterly, which is a
OL,14,Fchillier air source at this time of
OL,15,Fyear - hence those lower temperatures
OL,16,F(mid rather than high teens).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774033869
OL,3,CWarm and sunny weekend - but a cold
OL,4,Csnap brings snow risk next week
OL,6,FThen on Tuesday night into Wednesday,
OL,7,Fa cold front will move southwards
OL,8,Facross the UK and this might well have
OL,9,Fsome snow on it, with wintry showers
OL,10,Ffollowing in behind.
OL,12,FThe wind turns to a cold northerly
OL,13,Fbehind that cold front and it's that
OL,14,FArctic air that will pull our
OL,15,Ftemperatures well down again - with
OL,16,Fdaytime highs expected to be into the
OL,17,Fhigh single figures for many - which
OL,18,Fis below average for the time of year.
OL,20,FWe've had some big temperature swings
OL,21,Fthis week ` what's going on?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1774033869
OL,3,CWarm and sunny weekend - but a cold
OL,4,Csnap brings snow risk next week
OL,6,FIt's in large part down to the clear
OL,7,Fovernight skies we've seen.
OL,9,FCloud acts like a blanket over the
OL,10,Fground; it's like an insulating layer
OL,11,Fthat prevents overnight temperatures
OL,12,Ffrom dropping away too much. With
OL,13,Fclear skies, the air cools very
OL,14,Fquickly which has meant cold, frosty
OL,15,Fstarts for many this week.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
